    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim 0.12 crashes with `lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:969: table index is nil` when\nan LSP client sends `client/registerCapability` with a method name not present\nin `lsp.protocol._request_name_to_server_capability`.\n\nThis affects proprietary/non-standard LSP methods (e.g. `tabby/chat`). After\ncommit `ed562c29` (PR #37161, ~March 2025), the registration lookup [changed](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37161/changes#diff-d932add3ce248b733b3f90f554b6c730db0d6c4e6a62ba08b8b32d2c6a75c918R933)\nfrom a safe keyed access to `self.registrations[method]` to a two-step lookup:\nfirst resolving `lsp.protocol._request_name_to_server_capability[method]`\n(returns `nil` for unknown methods), then using that as a key into\n`self.registrations[nil]`, which crashes under LuaJIT's table indexing.\n\n### Related\n\n- [#37166](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37166) \"Better LSP Dynamic Registration Handling\" - feature request, not crash-related\n- [#37895](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37895) \"LSP SERVER_REQUEST_HANDLER_ERROR in lua/vim/lsp/client.lua\" - related LSP crash\n- [TabbyML/vim-tabby#40](https://github.com/TabbyML/vim-tabby/issues/40) - upstream discussion of the `tabby/chat` registration\n- [PR #37161](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37161) - \"fix(lsp): improve dynamic registration handling\" (regressionp)\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n### /tmp/min_config.lua\n\n```lua\nlocal cmd = { 'python3', '/tmp/mock_lsp_server.py' }\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimEnter', {\n  once = true,\n  callback = function()\n    vim.lsp.start({\n      name = 'mock-lsp',\n      cmd = cmd,\n      root_dir = vim.fn.getcwd(),\n    })\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n### /tmp/mock_lsp_server.py\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Minimal LSP stdio server that triggers the client/registerCapability crash.\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ndef send(method, params=None, msg_id=None):\n    msg = {\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\"}\n    if msg_id is not None:\n        msg[\"id\"] = msg_id\n    msg[\"method\"] = method\n    if params is not None:\n        msg[\"params\"] = params\n    body = json.dumps(msg).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    sys.stdout.buffer.write(f\"Content-Length: {len(body)}\\r\\n\\r\\n\".encode())\n    sys.stdout.buffer.write(body)\n    sys.stdout.buffer.flush()\n\ndef read_request():\n    headers = {}\n    while True:\n        line = sys.stdin.buffer.readline()\n        if line in (b\"\", b\"\\r\\n\", b\"\\n\"):\n            break\n        decoded = line.decode(\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\").strip()\n        if decoded.lower().startswith(\"content-length:\"):\n            headers[\"content-length\"] = int(decoded.split(\":\", 1)[1].strip())\n    length = headers.get(\"content-length\", 0)\n    if length == 0:\n        return None\n    raw = sys.stdin.buffer.read(length)\n    return json.loads(raw.decode(\"utf-8\"))\n\ninit_req = read_request()\nif init_req:\n    send(\"notifications/initialized\")\n    send(\"initialize\", {\"capabilities\": {}}, init_req.get(\"id\"))\n    send(\"client/registerCapability\", {\n        \"registrations\": [\n            {\n                \"id\": \"tabby-registration\",\n                \"method\": \"workspace/fakeMethod\",\n                \"registerOptions\": {},\n            }\n        ],\n    })\nsys.exit(0)\n```\n\n### Reproduction\n\n```bash\nchmod +x /tmp/mock_lsp_server.py\nnvim --clean -u /tmp/min_config.lua\n```\n\nNeovim lsp client crashes with `table index is nil` at the bottom of the window.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should gracefully handle unknown method names in\n`client/registerCapability` - either ignoring them with a notification, or\nstoring them in a per-client fallback table as it did before PR #37161.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nMock Server (originally identified while using tabby-agent from TabbyML/tabby)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixos Unstable\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/datGryphon/25549d58af4f512122499da7e5556692\n\n#### Edit\n\n- add link to relevant line change in description\n- punctuation and formatting",
