        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk, thank you for looking into it. That PR you mentioned fixes a related bug in `_support_registration` but does not address the underlying bug in `_register_dynamic`. \n\nHere's the traceback after building and reproducing on the latest master: \n\n```\n➜  neovim git:(master) VIMRUNTIME=runtime build/bin/nvim --clean -u /tmp/min_config.lua --headless\nvim.schedule callback: runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:984: table index is nil\nstack traceback:\n\truntime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:984: in function '_register_dynamic'\n\truntime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:992: in function '_register'\n\truntime/lua/vim/lsp/handlers.lua:149: in function 'handler'\n\truntime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:1315: in function '_notification'\n\truntime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:482: in function 'fn'\n\t[string \"vim/_core/editor\"]:404: in function <[string \"vim/_core/editor\"]:403>\n^CNvim: Caught deadly signal 'SIGINT'\nNvim: Finished.\n```\n\nMinimal patch I am looking at which fixes the immediate bug but I haven't dug deeper on validating. \n\n```\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua\nindex bc8e68f..00445c7 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua\n@@ -961,6 +961,9 @@ function Client:_supports_registration(method)\n     return true\n   end\n   local provider = self:_registration_provider(method)\n+  if not provider then\n+    return false\n+  end\n   local capability_path = lsp.protocol._provider_to_client_registration[provider]\n   local capability = vim.tbl_get(self.capabilities, unpack(capability_path))\n   return type(capability) == 'table' and capability.dynamicRegistration\n@@ -980,10 +983,12 @@ function Client:_register_dynamic(registrations)\n   self:_unregister_dynamic(registrations)\n   for _, reg in ipairs(registrations) do\n     local provider = self:_registration_provider(reg.method)\n-    if not self.registrations[provider] then\n-      self.registrations[provider] = {}\n+    if provider then\n+      if not self.registrations[provider] then\n+        self.registrations[provider] = {}\n+      end\n+      table.insert(self.registrations[provider], reg)\n     end\n-    table.insert(self.registrations[provider], reg)\n   end\n end\n```\n\nLet me know if there's anything else I can help with.\n\nEdit: added patch",
